== Install ==
=== Warnings ===
'''Wickr is non-free software. Discouraged as per [[Avoid nonfree software]]!'''

'''This can lead to breaking the package upgrading system!''' This is because we are mixing Debian (which Whonix is based on) with Ubuntu software sources. <ref>For better stability Wickr.com would to provide Debian downloads or even better an apt repository for Debian.</ref>

This is counter to best practices on the [[Install Software]] page. Therefore use a separate Whonix-Workstation.

=== Open Terminal ===
{{Open a Whonix-Workstation Terminal}}

=== APT Signing Key ===
Add Ubuntu's apt signing key.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-key --keyring /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/ubuntu.gpg adv --keyserver hkp://qdigse2yzvuglcix.onion --recv-keys 630239CC130E1A7FD81A27B140976EAF437D05B5
}}

Expected output.

<pre>
Executing: /tmp/apt-key-gpghome.6Ouq0wKoVF/gpg.1.sh --keyserver hkp://qdigse2yzvuglcix.onion --recv-keys 630239CC130E1A7FD81A27B140976EAF437D05B5
key 40976EAF437D05B5:
59 signatures not checked due to missing keys
gpg: key 40976EAF437D05B5: public key "Ubuntu Archive Automatic Signing Key <ftpmaster@ubuntu.com>" imported
gpg: Total number processed: 1
gpg:               imported: 1
</pre>

=== APT Sources ===
<ref>
Created using 
https://repogen.simplylinux.ch/#
</ref> <ref>
https://me-download.wickr.com/#/version/me says Ubuntu 16.04 which is xenial.
</ref>

A new file <code>/etc/apt/sources.list.d/ubuntu.list</code> containing the Ubuntu repository has to be created.

{{Open with root rights|filename=
/etc/apt/sources.list.d/ubuntu.list
}}

Paste.

{{CodeSelect|code=
###### Ubuntu Main Repos
deb http://uk.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ xenial main 

###### Ubuntu Update Repos
deb http://uk.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ xenial-security main 
deb http://uk.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ xenial-updates main 
}}

Save.

=== Dependencies ===
{{Update}}

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-get update
}}

Install dependencies.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-get install libhunspell-1.3 libprotobuf9v5 libpng12-0
}}

=== Download ===
{{Manual Software Installation}}

Download WickrMe from https://me-download.wickr.com/#/version/me. Choose the Ubuntu version. <ref>
* https://wickr.com/
* https://support.wickr.com/hc/en-us/articles/115003136873-How-to-Install-on-Linux
</ref>

Save in <code>~/Downloads</code> folder. (Hint [[Tor Browser#Navigating Tor Browser Downloads]].)

At the time of writing, no software signatures were provided.

=== Change Directory ===
Change to Downloads folder.

{{CodeSelect|code=
cd ~/Downloads
}}

=== Extract ===
Unzip.

{{CodeSelect|code=
unzip WickrMe*.zip
}}

=== Install ===
Install WickrQt. <ref>
Replaced gdebi with dpkg. It's just a deb. Dpkg should be very very much fine. Even easier to debug than graphical frontend gdebi.
</ref>

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo dpkg -i wickr-qt_*_amd64.deb
}}

Install WickrMe.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo dpkg -i WickrMe_*_amd64.deb
}}

=== Fixes ===
Fix dependencies.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-get install -f
}}

Download <code>libgstreamer-plugins-good1.0-0</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
apt-get download libgstreamer-plugins-good1.0-0
}}

Fix packaging conflict (since we mix with Ubuntu).

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo dpkg --force-all --install libgstreamer-plugins-good*_amd64.deb
}}

Fix dependencies.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo apt-get install -f
}}

Last lines of output are expected to show something like:

<pre>
Setting up wickrme (4.59.10-01) ...
Processing triggers for libc-bin (2.24-11+deb9u3) ...
</pre>

=== Done ===
The installation process is now complete.

